TY  - JOUR
T1  - Understanding the Cross-Level Embeddedness of Interfirm Partnership Formation
AU  - Hagedoorn, John
Y1  - 2006/07/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2006.21318924
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2006.21318924
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 670
EP  - 680
VL  - 31
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper suggests a cross-level understanding of the embeddedness of interfirm partnering in the context of the formation of new partnerships. It makes a critical distinction among environmental embeddedness, interorganizational embeddedness, and dyadic embeddedness, stressing the importance of understanding the interaction of these different levels of embeddedness. This focus on the complex interaction effects of different levels of embeddedness of interfirm partnering sets this contribution apart from previous work in the field.
